<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-04-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-04-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="853" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d853">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 882.51/322.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">General Receiver</gloss> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-05">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 5, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>I understand from Falkner’s memorandum<note n="1" xml:id="d853fn1">Not
                                printed.</note> that German Receiver must be stationed permanently
                            at or near Monrovia. Attitude here, as stated by Minister Cromelin, is
                            that receivers should rotate, and that any other arrangement would be
                            unfortunate. Am convinced that agreement affecting German Receiver would
                            necessarily become public eventually, and that effect of such agreement
                            would be to split receivership into two factions, thus making success
                            difficult. Await instructions in the premises.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Clark.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>